.\" SSG - Static Site Generator
.\" Man page for ssg(1)
.TH SSG 1 "2026-03-31" "1.7.4" "SSG Manual"
.SH NAME
ssg \- fast static site generator written in Go
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ssg
.I source template domain
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B ssg
.B \-\-config
.I file
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B ssg
.B \-\-mddb\-url\fR=\fIURL
.B \-\-mddb\-collection\fR=\fINAME
.I template domain
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ssg
is a fast and flexible static site generator that converts Markdown content
with YAML frontmatter into static HTML websites. It supports multiple template
engines (Go, Pongo2/Jinja2, Mustache, Handlebars), WebP image conversion,
built-in HTTP server with live reload, and deployment packaging for
Cloudflare Pages.
.PP
SSG can read content from local Markdown files or from a remote MDDB
(Markdown Database) server via HTTP or gRPC.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I source
Content source folder name (inside content-dir). Not required when using
MDDB content source.
.TP
.I template
Template name (inside templates-dir).
.TP
.I domain
Target domain for the generated site (e.g., example.com).
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Configuration
.TP
.BR \-\-config =\fIFILE
Load configuration from a YAML, TOML, or JSON file. If not specified,
auto-detects \fB.ssg.yaml\fR, \fB.ssg.toml\fR, or \fB.ssg.json\fR in the
current directory.
.SS Template Engine
.TP
.BR \-\-engine =\fIENGINE
Template engine to use. Available engines:
.BR go " (default),"
.BR pongo2 " (Jinja2/Django-like),"
.BR mustache ","
.BR handlebars .
.TP
.BR \-\-online\-theme =\fIURL
Download theme from a URL. Supports GitHub, GitLab repositories, or direct
ZIP file URLs.
.SS MDDB Content Source
.TP
.BR \-\-mddb\-url =\fIURL
MDDB server URL. Enables MDDB mode. Use \fBhttp://localhost:11023\fR for
HTTP or \fBlocalhost:11024\fR for gRPC.
.TP
.BR \-\-mddb\-protocol =\fIPROTO
Connection protocol: \fBhttp\fR (default) or \fBgrpc\fR.
.TP
.BR \-\-mddb\-collection =\fINAME
Collection name for fetching pages and posts.
.TP
.BR \-\-mddb\-key =\fIKEY
API key for MDDB authentication (optional).
.TP
.BR \-\-mddb\-lang =\fILANG
Language filter for MDDB documents (e.g., \fBen_US\fR, \fBpl_PL\fR).
.TP
.BR \-\-mddb\-timeout =\fISEC
Request timeout in seconds (default: 30).
.TP
.BR \-\-mddb\-batch\-size =\fIN
Batch size for pagination when fetching documents (default: 1000).
.TP
.B \-\-mddb\-watch
Watch MDDB for content changes and rebuild automatically.
.TP
.BR \-\-mddb\-watch\-interval =\fISEC
Polling interval for MDDB watch mode in seconds (default: 30).
.SS Server & Development
.TP
.B \-\-http
Start the built-in HTTP server after generating the site.
.TP
.BR \-\-port =\fIPORT
HTTP server port (default: 8888).
.TP
.B \-\-watch
Watch content and template directories for file changes and rebuild
automatically.
.TP
.B \-\-clean
Remove the output directory before building.
.SS Output Control
.TP
.B \-\-sitemap\-off
Disable sitemap.xml generation.
.PP
Pages and posts are automatically excluded from sitemap.xml when any of the
following frontmatter conditions are met:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\fBrobots\fR contains \fBnoindex\fR (e.g. \fBrobots: "noindex, follow"\fR)
.IP \(bu 2
\fBlayout: "redirect"\fR
.IP \(bu 2
\fBsitemap: "no"\fR
.RE
.TP
.B \-\-robots\-off
Disable robots.txt generation.
.TP
.BR \-\-pretty\-html ", " \-\-pretty
Clean up generated HTML by removing all blank lines, without aggressive
minification.
.TP
.B \-\-relative\-links
Convert absolute URLs containing the site domain to relative links.
Supports href, src, action attributes and url() in inline styles.
.TP
.BR \-\-post\-url\-format =\fIFMT
Post URL format. Options:
.RS
.TP
.B date
Date-based URLs: \fB/YYYY/MM/DD/slug/\fR (default).
.TP
.B slug
SEO-friendly slug-only URLs: \fB/slug/\fR.
.RE
.TP
.BR \-\-page\-format =\fIFMT
Page output format. Controls how HTML files are generated. Options:
.RS
.TP
.B directory
Each page generates \fBslug/index.html\fR (default). URLs end with
trailing slash: \fB/slug/\fR.
.TP
.B flat
Each page generates \fBslug.html\fR. URLs include the extension:
\fB/slug.html\fR.
.TP
.B both
Generates both \fBslug/index.html\fR and \fBslug.html\fR for maximum
compatibility. URLs use the directory form: \fB/slug/\fR.
.RE
.TP
.B \-\-minify\-all
Minify HTML, CSS, and JS output.
.TP
.B \-\-minify\-html
Minify only HTML output.
.TP
.B \-\-minify\-css
Minify only CSS output.
.TP
.B \-\-minify\-js
Minify only JS output.
.TP
.B \-\-sourcemap
Include source maps in output.
.SS Image Processing
.TP
.B \-\-webp
Convert images to WebP format. Requires \fBcwebp\fR to be installed.
.TP
.BR \-\-webp\-quality =\fIN
WebP compression quality, 1\-100 (default: 60).
.TP
.B \-\-reconvert\-images
Force reconversion of images even if WebP versions already exist.
.SS Deployment
.TP
.B \-\-zip
Create a ZIP deployment package for Cloudflare Pages.
.SS Paths
.TP
.BR \-\-content\-dir =\fIPATH
Content directory (default: \fBcontent\fR).
.TP
.BR \-\-templates\-dir =\fIPATH
Templates directory (default: \fBtemplates\fR).
.TP
.BR \-\-output\-dir =\fIPATH
Output directory (default: \fBoutput\fR).
.SS Other
.TP
.BR \-\-quiet ", " \-q
Suppress all output; only exit codes indicate success or failure.
.TP
.BR \-\-version ", " \-v
Print the version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-\-help ", " \-h
Print usage information and exit.
.SH CONFIGURATION FILE
SSG supports configuration via YAML, TOML, or JSON files. The config file
is specified with \fB\-\-config\fR or auto-detected as \fB.ssg.yaml\fR,
\fB.ssg.toml\fR, or \fB.ssg.json\fR.
.PP
Example \fB.ssg.yaml\fR:
.PP
.RS
.nf
source: "my-content"
template: "simple"
domain: "example.com"
webp: true
webp_quality: 80
pretty_html: true
post_url_format: "slug"
engine: "go"

shortcodes:
  - name: "promo"
    template: "shortcodes/banner.html"
    title: "Special Offer"
    text: "Get 50% off!"
    url: "https://example.com"

variables:
  gtm: "GTM-XXXXXXX"
  analytics_id: "$GA_ID"
  api:
    endpoint: "https://api.example.com"

pages_path: "docs"
posts_path: "articles"
rewrite_md_links: true
preserve_slug_case: false

mddb:
  enabled: true
  url: "http://localhost:11023"
  collection: "blog"
  protocol: "http"
  lang: "en_US"
  watch: true
  watch_interval: 30
.fi
.RE
.SH CONTENT PATHS
By default SSG reads static pages from the \fBpages/\fR subdirectory and blog
posts from the \fBposts/\fR subdirectory inside the content source. Both can be
overridden:
.TP
.B pages_path
Subdirectory name for static pages (default: \fBpages\fR).
Example: \fBpages_path: "docs"\fR reads from \fBcontent/{source}/docs/\fR.
.TP
.B posts_path
Subdirectory name for blog posts (default: \fBposts\fR).
Example: \fBposts_path: "articles"\fR reads from \fBcontent/{source}/articles/\fR.
.SH SLUG HANDLING
Slugs are read from the \fBslug:\fR field in frontmatter. When no slug is set,
it is automatically derived from the source filename (without the \fB.md\fR
extension).
.PP
By default slugs are lowercased (\fBAPI.md\fR → \fB/api/\fR). Set
\fBpreserve_slug_case: true\fR to keep the original casing (\fBAPI.md\fR →
\fB/API/\fR).
.SH MD LINK REWRITING
When \fBrewrite_md_links: true\fR is set, relative \fB.md\fR hrefs in content
are rewritten to their final output URLs during the build.
.PP
For example \fBhref="AUTHENTICATION.md"\fR becomes
\fBhref="/authentication/"\fR (or whatever the slug resolves to).
.PP
Relative path prefixes (\fB./\fR, \fB../dir/\fR) are stripped — only the base
filename is matched. Unknown \fB.md\fR links are left untouched. The feature is
opt-in to avoid breaking sites that intentionally serve raw \fB.md\fR files.
.SH CONFIG VARIABLES
Define custom variables in \fB.ssg.yaml\fR under the \fBvariables\fR key. They are
available in every template context as \fB{{.Vars.key}}\fR and exported as
environment variables with the \fBSSG_\fR prefix at build time.
.PP
Nested maps are supported: \fB{{.Vars.api.endpoint}}\fR is exported as
\fBSSG_API_ENDPOINT\fR.
.PP
Values starting with \fB$\fR are resolved from the current OS environment
(e.g. \fB"$GTM_CODE"\fR reads the \fBGTM_CODE\fR env var). If the env var is not
set the literal value is kept unchanged.
.PP
Example:
.RS
.nf
variables:
  gtm: "GTM-XXXXXXX"        # {{.Vars.gtm}}, exported as SSG_GTM
  analytics_id: "$GA_ID"    # resolved from $GA_ID at build time
  api:
    endpoint: "https://api.example.com"  # SSG_API_ENDPOINT
.fi
.RE
.SH TEMPLATE ENGINES
SSG supports four template engines:
.TP
.B go
Go's standard \fBhtml/template\fR package (default). Uses \fB{{ .Field }}\fR
syntax.
.TP
.B pongo2
Jinja2/Django-like templates. Uses \fB{{ field }}\fR and
\fB{% block %}\fR syntax.
.TP
.B mustache
Logic-less templates. Uses \fB{{field}}\fR and \fB{{#section}}\fR syntax.
.TP
.B handlebars
Extension of Mustache with helpers. Uses \fB{{field}}\fR and
\fB{{#if condition}}\fR syntax.
.SH TEMPLATE VARIABLES
All page/post fields are available at the template root level for direct access.
Custom metadata fields from MDDB frontmatter are also flattened to root level.
.PP
.B Standard fields:
.RS
.nf
{{ .Title }}        \- Page/post title
{{ .Slug }}         \- URL slug
{{ .Content }}      \- Rendered HTML content
{{ .Date }}         \- Publication date
{{ .Modified }}     \- Last modification date
{{ .Excerpt }}      \- Content excerpt
{{ .URL }}          \- Page URL path
{{ .CanonicalURL }} \- Full canonical URL
{{ .Description }}  \- SEO description
{{ .Keywords }}     \- SEO keywords
{{ .Tags }}         \- Tags array
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Custom fields (from MDDB metadata):
.RS
.nf
{{ .dupa }}         \- Custom field "dupa"
{{ .defaultVideo }} \- Custom field "defaultVideo"
{{ .playlist }}     \- Custom field "playlist"
.fi
.RE
.PP
For backward compatibility, \fB{{ .Page.Title }}\fR and \fB{{ .Post.Title }}\fR
still work.
.SH CO-LOCATED ASSETS
Images and other media files placed alongside Markdown content files are
automatically copied to the corresponding output directory. This allows
you to reference images with simple relative paths in your Markdown.
.PP
For example, if you have:
.PP
.RS
.nf
content/my-site/pages/about.md
content/my-site/pages/about-photo.png
.fi
.RE
.PP
The \fBabout-photo.png\fR will be copied to \fBoutput/about/about-photo.png\fR,
and you can reference it in \fBabout.md\fR as:
.PP
.RS
.nf
![Photo](about-photo.png)
.fi
.RE
.PP
Supported asset types: PNG, JPG, JPEG, GIF, SVG, WebP, ICO, BMP, TIFF,
AVIF, MP4, WebM, OGG, MP3, WAV, PDF, ZIP.
.SH BUILT-IN THEMES
.TP
.B simple
Modern dark theme with glassmorphism effects, purple gradient accents, and
micro-animations.
.TP
.B krowy
Light green farm theme inspired by krowy.net, with natural colors and
organic design.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful execution.
.TP
.B 1
Error during generation, invalid configuration, or missing required
arguments.
.SH EXAMPLES
Generate a site with the simple template:
.PP
.RS
.nf
ssg my-site simple example.com
.fi
.RE
.PP
Start development server with live reload:
.PP
.RS
.nf
ssg my-site simple example.com --http --watch
.fi
.RE
.PP
Build with minification and WebP conversion:
.PP
.RS
.nf
ssg my-site krowy example.com --clean --minify-all --webp --zip
.fi
.RE
.PP
Use Pongo2 template engine with an online theme:
.PP
.RS
.nf
ssg my-site mytheme example.com --engine=pongo2 \\
    --online-theme=https://github.com/user/hugo-theme
.fi
.RE
.PP
Use MDDB content source with gRPC:
.PP
.RS
.nf
ssg --mddb-url=localhost:11024 --mddb-protocol=grpc \\
    --mddb-collection=blog krowy example.com
.fi
.RE
.PP
Load all settings from config file:
.PP
.RS
.nf
ssg --config .ssg.yaml --http --watch
.fi
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I .ssg.yaml
Default YAML configuration file (auto-detected).
.TP
.I .ssg.toml
Default TOML configuration file (auto-detected).
.TP
.I .ssg.json
Default JSON configuration file (auto-detected).
.TP
.I content/
Default content directory containing Markdown files.
.TP
.I templates/
Default templates directory containing theme files.
.TP
.I output/
Default output directory for generated HTML.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
SSG does not use environment variables. All configuration is done via
command-line flags or configuration files.
